 my fault, but we wouldn't have dared - stay from school if our mother or father hadn't kept us off. And they would keep us off perhaps to go - some special - message or - no shoes, something like that, and - and I think that she - if it had been one of t
h
ose middle class girls - that was dressed nicer, she wouldn't have give the cane to - like us poor ragged children. I think that, mm. Looking back now. And I just said I - I was very scared to hold me hand out, and - I said, please sister, me mother said 
-
 if - if you caned me I haven't to come to this school anymore. Well you know that - made her very angry, in front of the class. And - she kept hold of me hand down and then the other one, oh I cried bitterly from about five past - ten past nine - to twel
ve o'clock, five to twelve.
