16. I - I was - four - exactly fourteen when I went into the mill. That would be 1916, yes. Sixteen - seventeen, eighteen, nineteen - I was married in 1925, but I did - about a year and a half - at - at Stockton in service, but it wasn't -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8282984 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4345194\charrsid9920055 Was this before you were married?
